And then Kamal Ghatak brought it with the help of Shambudas to...

00:01:48.500 --> 00:01:51.500
to the Parade in Cardiff.

00:01:51.500 --> 00:01:55.500
Right. Thank you very much, Anamika, for filling that up because...

00:01:55.500 --> 00:02:02.500
Anamika Chatterjee, she's also been involved same time as Kanhai Chatterjee,

00:02:02.500 --> 00:02:06.500
his good wife, and she's still involved in our puja.

00:02:06.500 --> 00:02:13.500
Can you, Kanhai, can you share some of your memories of the first puja when you attended it?

00:02:13.500 --> 00:02:17.500
What sort of puja it was like back in 1975?

00:02:17.500 --> 00:02:24.500
When we attended the puja, I remember particularly the ladies were involved much

00:02:24.500 --> 00:02:31.500
in actually making the puja offerings and taking somebody's house,

00:02:31.500 --> 00:02:36.500
like in Port Conde in our house and Auroghosa's house,

00:02:36.500 --> 00:02:41.500
and Roma Pachaudhuri's house in Cardiff,

00:02:41.500 --> 00:02:43.500
and...

00:02:43.500 --> 00:02:45.500
Can I join in?

00:02:45.500 --> 00:02:47.500
Yeah, yeah, come and join in. That's fine, yeah.

00:02:47.500 --> 00:02:54.500
Yes, I remember it because it was my first puja after coming from Kolkata, India,

00:02:54.500 --> 00:03:06.500
and I was a newly bride, so it was very exciting for me to go and see a durga puja happening in Wales, you know.

00:03:06.500 --> 00:03:10.500
So when I went there, there were lots of activities going on,

00:03:10.500 --> 00:03:16.500
but nowadays all the cooking and everything gets done in the hall.

00:03:16.500 --> 00:03:21.500
Those days we were not that lucky to have all the accommodation,

00:03:21.500 --> 00:03:27.500
so we only had a hall to have the puja, all the offerings, everything,

00:03:27.500 --> 00:03:34.500
but actual the feeding part where the loads of people come and have food with us,

00:03:34.500 --> 00:03:36.500
we didn't have that space.

00:03:37.500 --> 00:03:44.500
So I remember we used to come back to Puthkol to make rasagulla and Shikha Ghosh's house,

00:03:44.500 --> 00:03:53.500
and Dr Tapash Ghosh, his wife, Sampa Bosh, Gopa, myself, Roma Pachaudhuri,

00:03:53.500 --> 00:03:59.500
and we all used to go to Roma Pachaudhuri's house to make khichuri and labra,

00:03:59.500 --> 00:04:04.500
so we just divided all the cooking into different houses, you know.

00:04:04.500 --> 00:04:08.500
So we used to travel in the morning, come back at lunchtime,

00:04:08.500 --> 00:04:13.500
cook all the food for the people who were going to attend puja, and go back to Cardiff.

00:04:13.500 --> 00:04:17.500
So it was much more harder work that time.

00:04:17.500 --> 00:04:20.500
That's really fascinating, Anamika.

00:04:20.500 --> 00:04:25.500
Do you think that also, other than the community spirit,

00:04:25.500 --> 00:04:28.500
there was also a financial reason for this,

00:04:28.500 --> 00:04:36.500
that the organization was not very well-off at that time, or limited financial resources?

00:04:36.500 --> 00:04:44.500
I think so, because puja wasn't held, it was only the beginning of puja in Cardiff,

00:04:44.500 --> 00:04:49.500
so it wasn't held at a much bigger scale as it's happening now,

00:04:49.500 --> 00:04:55.500
so we had less resources, financial resources.

00:04:55.500 --> 00:05:00.500
I remember people used to come to our house, get khana,

00:05:00.500 --> 00:05:04.500
they used to go around people's houses to collect puja.

00:05:04.500 --> 00:05:10.500
I wanted to say, because the next question is number five, what made the challenges?

00:05:10.500 --> 00:05:17.500
So we'll come to the challenges, so just to complete what Anamika was saying,

00:05:17.500 --> 00:05:22.500
so you went around the houses to actually involve.

00:05:22.500 --> 00:05:28.500
So let's come to that, what were the challenges you both feel was at that time in the puja?

00:05:28.500 --> 00:05:35.500
I remember myself with Tapas Basu used to go in different places,

00:05:35.500 --> 00:05:39.500
in Cardiff, in Swansea, in other places, nearby places,

00:05:39.500 --> 00:05:47.500
to collect chala, what we call their contribution for the puja,

00:05:47.500 --> 00:05:55.500
and it was very difficult, because at that time we are not sure how many Indian people,

00:05:55.500 --> 00:06:02.500
particularly Bengali people, is around in Swansea areas, or even in Bridgen and Port Coor,

00:06:02.500 --> 00:06:07.500
and that was a major challenge we found out at that time.

00:06:07.500 --> 00:06:09.500
You want to add something?

00:06:09.500 --> 00:06:19.500
It was a challenge, because in relation to puja, what's happening now is there is much more publicity,

00:06:19.500 --> 00:06:26.500
advertisement, which attracts people to come to their nearest place to have Durga Puja,

00:06:26.500 --> 00:06:31.500
because this is a very special time for the Bengali all over India,

00:06:31.500 --> 00:06:36.500
its puja is held in different names. We call it Durga Puja,

00:06:36.500 --> 00:06:42.500
in some parts of India it's called something different, so it's very important to all Indians,

00:06:42.500 --> 00:06:49.500
but at that time we didn't have the measurement of publicity that much,

00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:53.500
so it was just word of mouth.

00:06:58.500 --> 00:07:03.500
So Anamika, you were saying that it was a lot of challenge, and Karnayita is saying a lot of challenge as well,

00:07:03.500 --> 00:07:09.500
how did you actually manage to identify people whose house to go to and knock for each other those days?

00:07:09.500 --> 00:07:18.500
That's by word of mouth, somebody I was asking where some Indian, particularly Bengali people were living,

00:07:18.500 --> 00:07:27.500
and of course the people who were around in this area, they were feeding us with all those addresses and the name of the people.

00:07:28.500 --> 00:07:39.500
Yes, it is like as an association, Indian association in Cardiff, we already knew quite a few people,

00:07:39.500 --> 00:07:44.500
doctors over the place, Bridgen, Swansea, Merthyr, Cardiff,

00:07:44.500 --> 00:07:54.500
so it was a challenge to collect donations and to run puja for six days.

00:07:55.500 --> 00:08:03.500
And of course a lot of people used to ring in our house to find out if there is any puja going on in the Indian East area,

00:08:03.500 --> 00:08:11.500
and that's also by word of mouth, and it started spreading all over Wales and outside.

00:08:11.500 --> 00:08:21.500
Just I wanted to concentrate a little bit about this time to connect, Chanda, and get the financial resources,

00:08:21.500 --> 00:08:28.500
because it's much more easier, I understand now, because everything is collected in the premises on four or five days,

00:08:28.500 --> 00:08:31.500
and people come there, we don't go to people's houses,

00:08:31.500 --> 00:08:40.500
and when you did that, it was before the days of internet, before the days of mobile phone, only the house sort of landline phones.

00:08:40.500 --> 00:08:49.500
Can you, both of you, can you give some experiences, bad and good experiences about going in people's house and collecting Chanda?

00:08:49.500 --> 00:08:53.500
Chanda, can you remember any bad or good experiences?

00:08:53.500 --> 00:09:05.500
I would say it was a rather interesting experience, because obviously Bengali people wanted to know if there is any Duga puja around the area,

00:09:05.500 --> 00:09:16.500
and they were very pleased to contribute whatever they can, and they did it very gladly, they accepted it,

00:09:16.500 --> 00:09:28.500
and obviously from them other people used to know what puja is going on, and that's how it started growing, the whole thing in there.

00:09:28.500 --> 00:09:31.500
Anamika, you want to add something on that?

00:09:31.500 --> 00:09:40.500
Well, I remember when I used to go out and collect donations for puja,

00:09:40.500 --> 00:09:51.500
obviously I didn't have first-hand experience, but what I used to have heard that sometimes it was a bit difficult sometimes,

00:09:51.500 --> 00:10:02.500
to go and ask for donations and wait for their perceptions of how they want to do it, you know,

00:10:02.500 --> 00:10:09.500
so I didn't have any first-hand experience, so I'm sorry I can't really add anything extra to it.

00:10:09.500 --> 00:10:18.500
So the Chanda collection at that time, probably each Chanda you got took probably half an hour, 45 minutes or an hour,

00:10:18.500 --> 00:10:25.500
because of the travel, then you have to discuss those with the people you are collecting the Chanda, and all that,

00:10:25.500 --> 00:10:31.500
and give them the information about the puja, which now it takes less than a couple of minutes.

00:10:31.500 --> 00:10:41.500
At that time of course it was time-taking, because you need some transport, not necessarily you always have the transport,

00:10:41.500 --> 00:10:50.500
you may have to go by bus to somebody's house, and that's how it happened, but at the end of the day we succeeded in collecting

00:10:51.500 --> 00:10:56.500
at least some contributions from the people involved.

00:10:56.500 --> 00:11:09.500
Can you remember anything which actually one thing or two things or three things which sticks out in your mind going back 40 years,

00:11:10.500 --> 00:11:11.500
which actually sticks out?

00:11:11.500 --> 00:11:21.500
The most important thing which sticks out in my mind is first of all is collecting Chanda, which is the contribution of people,

00:11:21.500 --> 00:11:33.500
and secondly to particularly to prepare offerings for the Goddess Durga, for example,

00:11:33.500 --> 00:11:43.500
that ladies were involved in cooking khichdi, labra, and making rasagullas in somebody's house,

00:11:43.500 --> 00:11:52.500
and these sort of things were really very exciting at that particular moment, and of course encouraged everybody to get involved,

00:11:52.500 --> 00:12:00.500
and a lot of volunteers then started coming in and saying can I do something, can I do this, and that's how it happened.

00:12:00.500 --> 00:12:02.500
You want to add something?

00:12:02.500 --> 00:12:15.500
Well for me it was something obviously I was so new, came to this country in 1975 April and Durga puja in October,

00:12:15.500 --> 00:12:28.500
so within five months I couldn't believe that something like this, a big gathering, it's not just religious, it's a social gathering as well,

00:12:28.500 --> 00:12:41.500
so to go there from the morning, meet so many people, and do all the work what was necessary to complete the puja,

00:12:41.500 --> 00:12:52.500
it was an overwhelming experience with friends, the people I didn't know, I met so many people, apart from the religious side of it,

00:12:52.500 --> 00:13:06.500
I wasn't that much involved in doing what I do now, but it's just a massive experience and it's a very joyful experience.

00:13:06.500 --> 00:13:19.500
So do you think that Durga puja and the festival going back in Wales for 40 years has actually helped in creating your circle and social contact?

00:13:19.500 --> 00:13:32.500
Of course it has, because this is the only opportunity once a year to go to Durga puja and meet lots of friends, make new friends,

00:13:32.500 --> 00:13:43.500
and by word of mouth the horizon, the boundaries started expanding, a lot of other people came to know,

00:13:43.500 --> 00:13:53.500
the people 70-80 miles away from Bristol used to come to the puja and of course it was the greatest opportunity to meet everybody,

00:13:53.500 --> 00:14:09.500
to exchange views, exchange gifts, know how their health or their wealth and how their children are doing,

00:14:09.500 --> 00:14:20.500
and all sorts of exchange of ideas, this took place and that is the greatest opportunity almost once a year for everybody to get together,

00:14:20.500 --> 00:14:29.500
and that's how the whole thing started growing in Wales, in particular in our Kadi puja.

00:14:29.500 --> 00:14:43.500
If I remember, 40 years ago, comparing in two days, of course the number of people at that particular time was not that many,

00:14:43.500 --> 00:14:56.500
what we can see now, we are more than about 2,500-3,000 people coming in over five days in recent years.

00:14:56.500 --> 00:15:11.500
Yes, it is just meeting everybody, people we don't meet regularly, we meet once a year there, and especially what fascinates me,

00:15:11.500 --> 00:15:28.500
now I'm talking about that all the youngsters are coming here to work and I go around and talk with them and it's a greatest pleasure for them,

00:15:28.500 --> 00:15:39.500
so young, coming here and attending Durga Puja, meeting people socially, it's a great pleasure.

00:15:39.500 --> 00:15:55.500
And do you think that in that interaction there is also an ongoing opportunity of transfer of experience about you or your life in this country or the society of this country

00:15:55.500 --> 00:16:03.500
to the younger people who have just come, they may ask you a few questions about the society, about other things which you may be able to help them with?

00:16:03.500 --> 00:16:15.500
Yes, definitely. Lots of youngsters we have met, they have asked me different questions, how was puja used to be or what did you do then, what should you do,

00:16:15.500 --> 00:16:31.500
so as an experienced person living in this country over 40 years, I think that's a lot of help to youngsters to settle them down well, so yes it is.

00:16:31.500 --> 00:16:44.500
I remember I used to work in a steel company and a lot of young people from India, from Tata Steel or Indian Steel Company, they used to visit to put talbot work,

00:16:44.500 --> 00:17:00.500
and of course some of them used to live in Port Coal and some used to live in Port Talbot, and they are of course very much interested being a Bengali person to find out if there are any Durga Puja going on,

00:17:00.500 --> 00:17:20.500
and that's how youngsters get involved, and once one group of people from India, they knew that Durga Puja is going on, but then from the water mouth, other people living in this area around 80 miles or 90 miles,

00:17:20.500 --> 00:17:33.500
they knew that Durga Puja is going on in the Cardiff area, and obviously they used to come there and enjoy themselves, and that's how the whole thing started growing up,

00:17:33.500 --> 00:17:53.500
and over the years since 40 years ago, and today we can see that a lot of people benefited by knowing that Puja is still going on and is still going well in that area.

00:17:53.500 --> 00:18:15.500
I understand, Kanahida, Anonymous as well, that in the last 15 years or so, you have actually been first helping and then being the main priest of Durga Puja. Can you tell us your experience about that and how you got involved like that?

00:18:15.500 --> 00:18:37.500
I remember in 2000, I had a phone call from Dr. Acharje, I called him Dada, he asked me over the telephone that whether I am interested in doing the Durga Puja.

00:18:37.500 --> 00:18:57.500
I was really very scared at that time because Durga Puja is not an easy thing to do, it needs a lot of involvement, and not only that, there was also what we call religious fear behind me,

00:18:57.500 --> 00:19:09.500
whether I am going to succeed, what is going to happen to me if I am not doing that thing particularly well, then I completely rejected the idea.

00:19:09.500 --> 00:19:26.500
Then Dr. Acharje came back to me again and asked me, Kanahida, there is nobody here who can perform the Puja, I was thinking you should be suitable for this opportunity.

00:19:26.500 --> 00:19:47.500
Then I told him that I have to ask my family in India whether I can actually perform the Puja ceremony, and I had a very good positive answer back from home,

00:19:47.500 --> 00:19:59.500
and I said to Acharje that of course as you asked me that there is nobody available, therefore put my name in, I will try my best.

00:19:59.500 --> 00:20:12.500
This way in year 2000, Dr. Acharje said you don't have to worry about anything, I am going to teach you everything from the very beginning,

00:20:12.500 --> 00:20:22.500
and therefore what happened was that about 3-4 months before the Durga Puja started, I started going to Dr. Acharje's house,

00:20:22.500 --> 00:20:38.500
and he showed me every nitty-gritty of the every day which I involved, and that's how it started, and of course the first year it was so difficult for me, I was a bit nervous,

00:20:38.500 --> 00:20:52.500
but once I started doing the first day what we call Shastri, then Saptami, Ostami, they all started becoming more and more easier for me,

00:20:52.500 --> 00:21:09.500
and I grew in confidence, and this way that year, it started in year 2000, I enjoyed very much to be honest, and for obvious reason I got hooked into this whole process.

00:21:09.500 --> 00:21:14.500
That's a good way of finishing that you got actually hooked into it.

00:21:14.500 --> 00:21:24.500
Anamika, tell me as Kanhai they are doing now Durga Puja, he is our main priest, he is actually the chief priest, how does it affect you?

00:21:24.500 --> 00:21:50.500
Well, as Kanhai is the priest, so I became his assistant you can say, but I had to learn lots of things from Mrs. Acharya, all the religious rituals which are very very complicated,

00:21:50.500 --> 00:22:10.500
and eventually I learnt it, like we all went to school and learnt various things in our life, very similar way, I learnt all the process, and why we do this, what it needs to be done, how many of this, how many of that,

00:22:10.500 --> 00:22:33.500
so I became very involved each year, so from 2000 year, 2000 till now, it's a huge responsibility, and I, since Mrs. Acharya passed away, I feel that the whole responsibility that is obviously after Kanhai is on my shoulder,

00:22:33.500 --> 00:22:53.500
I need to do everything, all the rituals as I have learnt, as best as I could, and I am also teaching youngsters how to do it, what to do, why we are doing it, what needs to be done on each day, so it's a big responsibility.

00:22:53.500 --> 00:23:04.500
So it's like what comes to me listening to both of you is going like a generational teaching from one generation to another generation.

00:23:23.500 --> 00:23:38.500
So he understands what he is doing, he did it religiously, and he is still doing it religiously, and that even makes me feel more responsible, so to do my part sincerely.

00:23:39.500 --> 00:23:41.500
That's great. What do you say about that?

00:23:41.500 --> 00:24:02.500
Kanhai, can you just say first that how you think the puja has actually grown and evolved in last sort of 25, 30 or 40 years, how you feel about how the puja has grown, the festival has grown?

00:24:02.500 --> 00:24:23.500
Obviously the Durgapuja is very much of a social as well as religious event, and the people who are particularly Bengali, they are interested to find out that is there any puja going on in Cardiff area,

00:24:23.500 --> 00:24:48.500
and from the word of mouth and to their friends it started, and a lot of people for the over the years like young doctors, young steelworkers, engineers started in about 70, 80 miles area around Cardiff,

00:24:48.500 --> 00:25:05.500
and they were all interested to come into the puja, and in last 20 years, last 15 years which I have been involved as a priest, I have noticed there was almost a steady growth of people,

00:25:05.500 --> 00:25:28.500
and over 15 years I am not sure whether that due to what they like my puja, I mean my performance during the puja ceremony, and in this way a lot of people got involved over the years,

00:25:28.500 --> 00:25:50.500
and still growing, and now we got a new generation of youngsters who became member of the wealth puja committee, and they have shown very much interest in doing whatever is required to do,

00:25:50.500 --> 00:26:11.500
and in this way I find out the festival particularly the number of people started growing, and the frontiers, the horizon started expanding over the years, and of course I am very much pleased and get a lot of pleasure out of it,

00:26:11.500 --> 00:26:18.500
knowing that people are still interested and they contribute whatever they can over the years.

00:26:18.500 --> 00:26:19.500
Can I come into it?

00:26:19.500 --> 00:26:21.500
Yes, Sonamika you come into it.

00:26:21.500 --> 00:26:39.500
You said how the puja evolved since last 25, 30 years, the main theme of the puja is still very similar, like it is a very family oriented, very friendly way, like 40 years ago I have seen it,

00:26:39.500 --> 00:26:58.500
it just grown in numbers, and it is still very friendly, we welcome everybody, but now I think we got high tech people here, the publicity of Kharif Durga Puja is huge,

00:26:58.500 --> 00:27:19.500
internet, mobile, telephone calls, letters, these are so many media that we publicize puja, so puja has evolved around since 1975, it is much larger scale,

00:27:19.500 --> 00:27:39.500
and all these committee people they have taken their responsibilities very very well, 1975 I didn't know that much, 1970 or what used to go on, but what I used to see there are few people, they always did the work,

00:27:39.500 --> 00:27:54.500
and I don't know whether there was a committee, I'm sure there was, but I'm not sure, but because of high tech, different social media, people's time contributions, everything means a lot more,

00:27:54.500 --> 00:28:21.500
and puja has grown into much bigger scale than I used to know it, 1975 till 1980s, nowadays, wow, people travel, even from Swindon, North Wales, just think about it, how much sincere people are to attend this religious and social festival?

00:28:21.500 --> 00:28:46.500
And of course, last year, the influence of the high tech, we can see that they are trying to interchange what is going on in Calcutta, and what is going on in Kharif in particular time,

00:28:46.500 --> 00:29:01.500
they are trying to show the whole puja ceremony, all the rituals, the people involved, and it is only possible because of the growth of what we call the high tech technology,

00:29:01.500 --> 00:29:20.500
and I remember that particularly when I saw on television that they are showing some excerpts from the Durga Puja in Kharif and in Calcutta.

00:29:20.500 --> 00:29:43.500
Do you think that coming to another angle, that Polyonomica can fully go on first, do you think there is also an angle has changed in terms of cultural activity or programs or functions, or do you think this is the same sort of way it used to be 30-40 years ago?

00:29:43.500 --> 00:29:53.500
Cultural function is going, involvement of people in cultural function is happening in much more larger scales.

00:29:53.500 --> 00:30:08.500
It also happened because I remember my two little girls, they joined into doing various things, various programs, but because Kharif Indian community was in a much smaller community,

